By a happy coincidence, the paramedics on my side of the room, they saw an ad in their circle of friends for a free meal at the today convenience store, and they communicated easily enough to get their 100 meals done.

On second thought, I'll give it a shot, ask them for the Didi driver's meal. Because Didi drivers are also very hard, also can not eat, they are in the first line to escort medical staff to and from work, is also a link in the whole chain.

So I talked to today, and I said, "can you see if you can get them some? "? It's a small order, about 300 copies a day, and I have people who distribute them, and I can write you anything you want. They were also photographed with their ID cards, saying "this meal is only for the distribution of Didi drivers" , were also pulled into the group, and their daily pictures were fed back to them. They agreed.

Then there was the larger issue of today's warehouse in an industrial district that had to be sanitized and controlled for two days before it had to close.

He was serving 15,800 meals a day, the equivalent of more than 8,000 people eating lunch, dinner. I need to top up this 15,000 a day with instant noodles.

The first step is to find the source. After looking for a person, I said to him, you arrange a few people to a few professional market, shoot signboard above the boss's phone, the boss should be a dealer, to find a way to the manufacturers;

The second link is to contact today: Tomorrow is not necessarily not open, then you give me all your supply and demand table, you this 15,000 meals sent to where, to whom, name, address, telephone, number, all to me;

I'll get another accountant to break this list down, by region. I delivered 300 noodles per car a day, helping me figure out how many cars I needed; according to 25, less than two hours, the team was assembled.

I was surprised. I didn't think I could build a network of 15,000 instant noodles a day.

But for me, it was just an option at the time. I feel like I'm the one who got them from Ramen to Rice, and now I'm the one who got them from rice to Ramen, and I feel like it's totally inappropriate.

I think it's best to try again. At that time, there was a logistics minister in the East West Lake district. He had to deal with a team's demand for washing machines. As their reimbursement process was slow, he came to me. I got them all in place the next day. They had already been installed, so he thinks we both want the same thing, that we're both paramedics. I told him about it, and he said yes. He gave me a way to get in touch.

I contacted the epidemic prevention coordination office and said, what kind of problem did I have with my request: that you may not know that there is a company in your industrial park called today, which has been providing free meals for 7,800 people every day since the beginning of the New Year, if they do shut down, 7,800 people could be affected. Do you think you can communicate with me? Is there any proof you can make up or something?

He said, "I'll put you in touch, and finally, the street leader. ". We need to negotiate and report back up, he said, knowing the seriousness of the problem.

The result: "Open tomorrow, but with a renewal. Not An emergency, but a renewal. " -- As if it were a green light.

The decisions he made, what was he carrying? I know. What he's carrying around, it could really be his career. Even if one of these people is infected by his lifestyle at home, he can't afford to keep this place closed. But he's willing to take the heat. He'll let you drive.

So, maybe it's an easy decision, everyone's contribution is really a lifetime thing, you know? His whole career, he decided that 7,800 people eating was more important than his career.

So... thanks to these people, everyone I've ever met, really.

8

Down Jackets, nail clippers, glasses

And then I started talking to the press, and the purpose of my talking to the press was to get donations of medical supplies. There's a team that helps me collect all the donations, and make a form for me; there's a team at Peking University, and they collect all the hospitals, and they contact them every day, and they only trust you, before he tells you what you really need, right? Because normally, with government supplies, why don't you have enough?

By the time you've built up a network of trust, say, 10,000 suits down, what's your gap? A thousand? Okay, I'll make up 1,000 pieces for your hospital, 400,600,500 for the other hospitals... all of them will return to him after receiving the goods, and the matter will be closed. In about two weeks, there should be over 20,000 pieces of medical supplies online and coming to me.

What kind of people do I target? Let me tell you about echelon, which is an unofficial term: First Echelon: shelter, Thor Mountain, these government supplies it is enough to manage, 130% , 150% guarantee, I manage you enough, you will not be poor; Second Echelon: Concord, the Pool of gold and silver, Tongji, this echelon is the main body of social donation, the government's supply is enough, 120% ; the third echelon, I can say a few hospitals, Puren, Wuhan Steel General Hospital... you hear very little words, then other donors do not know. They're also setting up fever clinics, these undonated hospitals, where the gap is going to get bigger, bigger, and after a few cycles there's no inventory, and a mask is going to be worn for three days, which is scary.

So my subject is what they are, what the few are involved in, where the power is not enough. Every time we cut into a medical team, I try to get the hotel to set up a group with a big Qr code at the door, and everyone adds to that group. What they found was a striking similarity, with the largest first round demand coming from the jacket jackets: too many of them came from out of town, not knowing how cold it was in winter in Wuhan.

When we received this request, we went to all the supermarkets to buy the down jackets for the waistcoats. I bought all of Wuhan when it opened. We ended up buying and donating, like, 3,000 of them. And Nail Clippers, and so on.

After the first set of requirements is collected, gather their other requirements. Because the first time, many people are very subtle, he will not tell you their real needs, sorry to tell you. Later, someone would like to talk about long Johns, we go to buy.

By the third round, it was basically a haircut: time for a haircut, too long.

And then there is the saying, "my phone can help me fix it, my phone screen broke" ... This is actually step by step trust, to that point, he will mention to you.

And then the glasses. The first is that the corner is crushed by the goggles. The second is that the glasses often fall off when you take them off. In fact, they think this is a personal matter, not a medical matter, in normal times, he can take a taxi to find a glasses shop? Not Now, no glasses shop open, no taxi for them to sit, no website of any kind to buy, no logistics..

Well, I'm just glad he's still willing to do it when we find someone who is. For example, we deal with at least two glasses a day, sometimes four. After the glasses of each hospital medical staff broke, we went to collect in the morning, and in the afternoon arranged with that person to pick him up from his community, to his glasses shop all repaired, and then returned to deal with the same day. We deal with three, we deal with one, right?

9

Now that it's on the news,

Now that medical supplies are out of my hands, what I'm working on now is, can I cooperate with some educational institutions that have found me and, according to what they say, record what kind of videos and what kind of teaching materials, what kind of educational function. I don't think I ever thought I'd be able to do that. Feel very... very proud, yes, it is possible that my children will see such a teaching material in the future, right?

As for my wife, the first big piece of news came to me, as if I knew she was going to get it sooner or later, so I told her in advance, "but don't let mom and dad know, they can't handle it. "

My parents found out February 13th. My mother saw the news, a phone call came over: "Wang Yong! Is it you! ? "

I want a name on the news. I want a video. Can you deny it? "It's me. "

Anyway, since it was on the news, my parents felt very proud. "You must be careful out there. " It was actually very weak, but my wife at home know that they did not sleep every day, can not sleep. For example, the most severe epidemic in the whole of China is in Hubei, the most severe epidemic in Hubei is in Wuhan, and the most severe epidemic in Wuhan is in the gold and Silver Lake. Your children actually went to the gold and Silver Lake to send medical staff to and from work. You said that a parent with flesh and blood, wouldn't he be worried? He's the only kid in his family. So they couldn't sleep at all, and my mom wasn't well

My daughter is too young, she does not understand, more than two years old, she only know that she usually play with a person is not at home. I've never been away from my daughter for more than 24 hours, and after leaving her for a month, she's bound to have a little something on her mind, and then she gets really cranky... so that's why I was thinking of going back early. On the last day after the first month, I went for a CT scan to make sure it was okay. I'll be home in two days. The day I went back, it was the first night my parents slept.

Looking back so many days... very happy ah, ha ha, got a lot of help, also let us help more people. They really thought that they had met me at their most difficult time, and I was grateful that I had been able to help them at their most difficult time. Thank you very much, and I hope more people will be willing to help others in the future.

March 5,2020

"We are experiencing the unexpected, the unexpected, the unexpected, " is the The Unbearable Lightness of Being word to describe these days.

In the city of Wuhan, where the pause button is suddenly pressed, there is both personal helplessness and mortal self-defense. Panic, pain, sadness, emotion... disaster, hard people become soft.

We want to record the history of Wuhan in the Spring of 2020 through the narration of 10 people.
